---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Text, LinkList, Box } from "@components/base";
import Header from "@components/sections/Header.astro";

import bigBarn from "../assets/home/barn.png";

const missionStatements = [
    "To regenerate soil health through holistic grazing practices that mimic nature's patterns",
    "To raise animals humanely, allowing them to express their natural behaviors on open pasture",
    "To produce nutrient-dense food without synthetic chemicals or harmful inputs",
    "To serve as stewards of the land, enhancing biodiversity and ecosystem resilience",
    "To connect our community directly to sustainable food systems through transparency and education",
];
---

<Layout currentPage="/">
    <Header slot="header">
        <div class="header_image">
            <Image
                src={bigBarn}
                alt="Sheep grazing on pasture along with chickens"
                width={375}
            />
        </div>
        <div class="header_subtext">
            <Text>
                Building a farm from scratch focused on regenerative
                agriculture. Giving opportunities for animals and plants to
                thrive off of each other. Work with nature, not bend it to our
                own desires.
            </Text>
        </div>
        <!-- <Link text="what we have planned" pathTo="/future-plans" /> -->
    </Header>

    <main slot="main">
        <Box>
            <Text tag="h3" slot="box_header"> Main Goals for farm </Text>
            <Text />
            <Text> Currently raising Katahdin cross with Dorper. </Text>
            <Text> Free range chickens for eggs. </Text>
            <Text>Exploring ways to build a regenerative farm</Text>
            <!-- <a href="resources/">Information on Regenerated Agriculture</a> -->
        </Box>

        <Box>
            <Text tag="h3" slot="box_header">Reasons why</Text>
            <Text>
                In 2015 one of children was diagnosed with brain cancer which
                lead us down a road of researching what was in our food and
                wanting to provide my family with good quality food. The event
                lead me to believe that the things we eat are able to provide
                our body the nutrients it needs to function properly and the
                help heal.
            </Text>
            <Text>
                Push back on industrialization of our food. What does that
                exactly mean? I don't think that all modern practices are bad,
                but we should evaluate them and look at a large scale of the
                impact of our decisions.
                <hr />
                Industrialization of food refers to the process of mass production
                and distribution of food products using industrial methods. This
                often involves the use of synthetic fertilizers, pesticides, and
                genetically modified organisms (GMOs), which can have negative impacts
                on the environment, human health, and animal welfare.
                <hr />
                I don't believe that animal are designed to be feed a diet that will
                grow them quickest, I believe that we are here to work with nature
                not to bend to what suits us.
            </Text>
            <!-- <a href="resources/">Information on Regenerated Agriculture</a> -->
        </Box>

        <Box>
            <Text tag="h3" slot="box_header">Farming background</Text>
            <Text>
                I grew up on a Dairy farm so livestock has always been a part of
                my life. I have had few flocks of chickens a couple of goats and
                a few cows and one rabbit. Mostly just as a hobby and joy having
                livestock around the house. There was a dry spell prior to 2022,
                then early that year is when we had the opportunity to bottle
                feed a couple of Rams. We had them in the house for a bit, the
                kiddos had a real laugh with the lambs running through the
                dinning room. Pastures where established and they where traded
                for a few ewes, now a flock of 15 and the desired of building my
                own farm with agriculture best practices.
            </Text>
            <!-- <Link text="On the farm" pathTo="/animals" /> -->
        </Box>

        <Box>
            <Text tag="h3" slot="box_header">Mission Statements</Text>
            <ul>
                {missionStatements.map((x) => <li>{x}</li>)}
            </ul>
        </Box>
    </main>
</Layout>
<style>
    h2,
    h3 {
        text-align: center;
    }
</style>
